<p>"The devil!" muttered Passepartout.</p>
<p>But a number of the passengers were at once attracted by the engineer's proposal, and Colonel Proctor was especially delighted, and found the plan a very feasible one.  He told stories about engineers leaping their trains over rivers without bridges, by putting on full steam; and many of those present avowed themselves of the engineer's mind.</p>
<p>"We have fifty chances out of a hundred of getting over," said one.</p>
